package se.swedenconnect.spring.saml.idp.attributes.release
Support for attribute release.

  • Class
    Description
    AttributeProducer
    An interface that is used to decide which attributes that should be released in an Assertion.
    AttributeReleaseManager
    The AttributeReleaseManager is an AttributeProducer configured with a list of AttributeProducers and a list of AttributeReleaseVoters.
    AttributeReleaseVote
    An enumeration acting as the result for a AttributeReleaseVoter.
    AttributeReleaseVoter
    AttributeReleaseVoters are used by the AttributeReleaseManager to check if attributes returned from AttributeProducers should be released or not.
    DefaultAttributeProducer
    The default AttributeProducer that returns all attributes that are among the "requested list" (see Saml2UserAuthentication.getAuthnRequirements()).
    DefaultAttributeReleaseManager
    Default implementation of the AttributeReleaseManager interface.
    IncludeAllAttributeReleaseVoter
    A voter that always votes AttributeReleaseVote.INCLUDE.
    ReleaseAllAttributeProducer
    An AttributeProducer that releases all attributes found in the supplied Saml2UserAuthenticationÂ token.
    SwedenConnectAttributeProducer
    An AttributeProducer that releases attributes according to the Technical Specifications for the Swedish eID Framework.
    SwedenConnectAttributeReleaseVoter
    A voter functioning according to the rules specified in Technical Specifications for the Swedish eID Framework.
